content:
Launch OmniScripts in Salesforce from Communities, Object detail pages, and Vlocity Card Actions.

How to Launch
Make an active OmniScript available for launch in one of four ways: as a standalone Lightning web component in a Lightning page, as an embedded link in another LWC, as a URL, or using an Aura wrapper.

Launching OmniScript from a Community or Lightning Record Page
The Vlocity LWC OmniScript Wrapper component hosts a single OmniScript that is invoked directly from a Community or Lightning Record Page. By default, the record Id that exists on a Lightning Record page passes as a parameter into the OmniScript as a context Id.

Launch OmniScript from a List Button
Configure an OmniScript to launch from a List button for a related list on a record page.

Launch an OmniScript From an Object Detail Page Using a Custom Link
To configure a custom link to launch an OmniScript from an object detail page, create a Visualforce page, then create the custom link and add it to the object's layout.

Creating a Custom Link to Launch an OmniScript
You can launch an OmniScript from any HTML page.

Launching an OmniScript From the Action Toolbar
Using the Action toolbar, you can launch a single OmniScript from a variety of contexts without configuring a Visualforce page for each context. For example, you can launch an OmniScript from a Contact, Account, Case record, or Customer Community, using a single Visualforce page.
title: Launching OmniScripts in Salesforce
